title._content: Mount Monadnock in Cheshire County, New Hampshire

description._content: TITLE Mount Monadnock in Cheshire County, New Hampshire CREATOR French, J.A., Keene NH SUBJECT Mountains - NH Monadnock, Mount (N.H.) DESCRIPTION Stereograph of "The Bluff" on Mount Monadnock, located in Cheshire County, New Hampshire. Monadnock is said to be the second most climbed mountain in the world, after Mt. Fuji. It is 3,165 feet tall and stands alone above the surrounding landscape. The geological term "monadnock" is taken from this mountain and means an isolated, erosin-resistant mountain that rises abruptly from its surroundings. PUBLISHER Keene Public Library and the Historical Society of Cheshire County DATE DIGITAL 20090727 DATE ORIGINAL 1870-1890?
